<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Opens Trade Fair in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi Tuesday called on all east African countries to harmonize
their economic policies and create more and better opportunities
for trade and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan president said this when he opened a week-long
international trade fair in the capital of Uganda Tuesday
afternoon, which has attracted exhibitors from 24 countries.
</P>
<P>
Economy, instead of politics, should play a bigger role in a
country's national life, he said.
</P>
<P>
The development of economy will provide more job opportunities
and improve people's livelihood, he added.
</P>
<P>
President Moi arrived here Tuesday morning and will return home
later in the day. 
