<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Russia Hope to Strengthen Defense Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Russia wanted to
broaden their defense cooperation following the talks between the
defense ministers of the two countries in Athens on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after meeting his Russian counterpart Igor Sergeyev on
the sidelines of the Defendory'98 arms exhibition which opened
Tuesday in Piraeus, Cyprus Defense Minister Yannakis Omirou said
that the two countries desired to broaden their defense
cooperation aimed at strengthening Cyprus' defenses and further
promoting the already excellent bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
As for the Russian-made S-300 anti-aircraft missiles to be
deployed in Cyprus later this year, Omirou said that they did not
discuss the matter, but added that their efforts were aimed at
returning the focus of the Cyprus problem to that of invasion and
occupation for it was certainly not one related to the arms
program of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also discussed the current political
situation in the Balkan region and jointly ascertained that the
danger of destabilization was being created due to Turkey's
behavior, particularly following Turkey's incursion into northern
Iraq and recent escalation of tension in its relations with Syria,
said the minister. 
</P>
