by the people of Uganda, Museveni said, adding that his name will
go down in the annals of the history of the heroic struggle
against oppression in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Brother to the Chief of Staff of Ugandan Army Brigadier James
Kazini, Mwebaze was believed to have died six days after the
plane, which was carrying altogether 10 people, crashed in the
mountain ranges on September 25.
</P>
<P>
He left Entebbe for Bunia and Beni in east of the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) aboard a Kenyan registered aircraft.
</P>
<P>
His pistol was later found with only five bullets left inside.
Military sources reportedly believe that he must have fired a few
times, possibly to alert the search party of his whereabouts.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the Ministry of Works, Transport and
Communication said five people have so far been rescued alive,
and three have died and two are still missing. 
