Automobiles Uganda Limited, said they have taken part in all the
international trade fairs since their company was established
here in 1995 because it provides potential business opportunities
for his company.
</P>
<P>
This week-long trade fair is widely believed to provide good
business opportunities for Uganda and to strengthen economic and
trade ties among the three east African countries.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, UMA Chairman James Wulwana said this
trade fair is a landmark of their standards.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to liberalization and macro-economic policies of the
government, Uganda's economy began to show signs of development,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Exhibitors from Nigeria, Libya and Eritrea are attending the
international trade fairs held in Uganda for the first time, the
UMA boss said.
</P>
