<HEADLINE> Yemen, Macedonia Establish Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Yemeni Republic and the
Republic of Macedonia have agreed to establish diplomatic ties on
ambassadorial level.
</P>
<P>
The ambassadors of Sanaa and Skobje signed a joint declaration
on the establishment of their diplomatic ties in London on
Tuesday, according to the Yemeni News Agency (YNA).
</P>
<P>
On the basis of their common desire to enhance friendly
relations and expand the horizons of cooperation in the political,
economic, cultural and humanitarian fields between them, Yemen and
Macedonia decided to establish diplomatic ties on the
ambassadorial level as of the date of signing the joint
declaration, YNA said.
</P>
<P>
Yemen and Macedonia believe that the diplomatic ties will help
the development of the close and friendly relations between the
governments and peoples of the two countries, the declaration
said. 
</P>
