<HEADLINE> Mubarak Arrives in Syria from Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak stopped over in Damascus, capital of Syria, on his way
back from Ankara to continue his mediation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at the Damascus International Airport, Mubarak
was met by Syrian President Hafez al-Assad and other top
officials. He later held talks with the Syrian side on the stance
of the Turkish leadership toward the Syrian-Turkish dispute.
</P>
<P>
In Ankara, Mubarak held talks for more than two hours with
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel on ways of defusing the
mounting tensions between Turkey and Syria.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long accused Syria of sheltering outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) rebels, who have been fighting since 1984 for
autonomy for the Kurdish minority in southeastern Turkey and
frequently wage cross-border raids on the Turkish military and
civilian targets from their camps in Iraq, Syria and Iran.
</P>
<P>
But Syria, together with Iran, has denied the charges, and
criticized, in return, Turkey for forming military alliance with
Israel that threatens the Arab security and undermines Syria's
bargaining position in the peace talks with the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Mubarak visited Syria where he held talks with
al-Assad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
