diplomats and reporter killed by the Afghan Taliban forces in
northern Afghanistan on Tuesday called for trying the Taliban
leaders for the crime.
</P>
<P>
The families made the call in a letter to the U.N.
Secretary General Kofi Annan delivered to visiting U.N. envoy
Lakhdar Ibrahimi, who arrived here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The letter, read in a meeting between Ibrahimi and the
families, called for immediate delivery of the bodies of three
other Iranian diplomats, which were still at the Taliban's hands,
the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of six Iranian diplomats and the IRNA reporter
were returned to Tehran last month.
</P>
<P>
The families also urged to identify and put on trial
those responsible for the killing of Iranians in Mazari Sharif,
northern Afghanistan, at an international court under the
supervision of the U.N..
</P>
<P>
The letter called on Annan to dispatch a fact-finding
mission to Afghanistan as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Ibrahimi expressed regret that the Iranian diplomats and
reporter were killed by the Taliban, saying that he would
informed the Pakistani and Taliban officials of Iran's demands.
</P>
