<HEADLINE> Moorsel Wins Elite Women's Time Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Dutch rider Leontien van
Moorsel gripped a precious home victory Wednesday in the elite
women's time trial of the World Cycling Championships in
Valkenburg, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Moorsel timed in 31 minutes and 51.14 seconds to highlight a
comeback victory for the Netherlands, who won the road
championship twice and the track title back in 1990.
</P>
