Quito and is expected to arrive on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's national team has never beaten Brazil in its 60-year
history.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's traveling roster was announced last week, which
includs three regulars from the 1988 World Cup runner-up squad in
the shape of defender Cafu, midfielder Rivaldo and forward
Denilson, along with several young players who are expected to
make the 2002 World Cup team.
</P>
<P>
The South Americans beat the United States 1-0 earlier in
Baltimore. 
