<HEADLINE> Beijing Develops Polluted Waste Water Treatment Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China has developed technology
to deal with waste water, according to the Sino-German seminar
that opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Water shortage and water pollution are two major problems in
half of China's 660 cities and 110 have a serious shortage of
water resources, resulting in billions of yuan in losses every
year.
</P>
<P>
The Nuclear Technology and Design Institute of Qinghua
University started cooperating in research in 1995 with Berlin
University of Technology on waste water treatment and recycling.
</P>
<P>
The new processing technology allows urban waste water to be
put back into underground streams, where it can be re-used.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and foreign scientists at the seminar will discuss
water resource control, water quality, and the technology of
waste water treatment and recycling. 
</P>
