measures against Syria" if Damascus does not back down on its
policy.
</P>
<P>
Ankara has long accused Damascus of sheltering PKK militants, a
charge denied by Syria. To show strength, Turkey has reportedly
massed troops backed by tanks and heavy artillery along the border
with Syria.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 for an independent Kurdish
state in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Syria have been at odds over issues including
Kurdish rebels, water sharing and Turkey's close military
cooperation with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Syria has accused Turkey of forging a military alliance with
the Jewish state, which it says will endanger the interests of the
Arab world and undermine its bargaining positions in the
negotiations with Israel. 
