<HEADLINE> Contact Group Likely to Meet in London Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The six-nation Contact Group
ministers on former Yugoslavia are likely to meet in London on
Thursday to discuss the Kosovo crisis, a Western diplomat said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The Foreign Office has already sent out the invitations and
it would be very surprising if the meeting did not go ahead as
planned," Reuters quoted the diplomat as saying.
</P>
<P>
Although the British Foreign Office declined to confirm whether
the meeting would take place, France and Russia on Wednesday said
they would send their foreign ministers Hubert Vedrine and Igor
Ivanov respectively to attend the talks.
</P>
<P>
The diplomat said the meeting would be the last chance to get
the Russians on board before NATO launches air strikes against
Yugoslavia over Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Russia has strongly opposed the idea of NATO air strikes against
Yugoslav forces without a specific United Nations Security Council
resolution and threated to veto the proposal of air strikes at the
UN Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The Contact Group comprises Britain, the United States,
Russia, Germany, Italy and France. 
