<HEADLINE> Philippine President to Meet Indonesian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada is set to meet with Indonesian President Bacharuddin Jusuf
Habibie in Singapore when they attend the World Economic Forum on
October 13.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed Wednesday by presidential spokesman Jerry
Barican in his regular press briefing with the media.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting was proposed by Indonesia's Coordinating
Economics Minister Karta Sasmita during his courtesy call with
President Estrada Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Barican said the meeting between the two leaders will be
finalized by the Philippine Department of Foreign Affairs and its
counterpart in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will discuss the bilateral relations, the
economic problems in the region and their effects including
political reform during their stay in Singapore, Barican said.
</P>
<P>
"That is very important to us because of our relations with
Indonesia, the immigration and refugee problems in the south and
also the relations on fishing and other natural resources rights
in the area," Barican said.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first meeting between the two presidents who
assumed office both this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
