<HEADLINE> Indian Air Force Mig-21 Aircraft Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- an Indian Air Force (IAF)
Mig-21 aircraft crashed at Nilgrant area of Kashmir killing the
pilot, a Defense Ministry spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The plane was on a routine training flight when it crashed
while negotiating a hilly area. The pilot, flight-lieutenant R. K.
Kamboj, who was wounded on board, later succumbed to his injuries,
he said.
</P>
<P>
