<HEADLINE> Beijing Gathering Marks Sino-Japanese Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of Chinese and
Japanese youth gathered here today to commemorate the 20th
anniversary of the signing of the Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace
and Friendship.
</P>
<P>
Liang Shi, vice-president of the China Association for
International Friendly Contact, said at the gathering that the
signing of the treaty marks a new era of comprehensive development
of the bilateral relationship.
</P>
<P>
Fruitful cooperation in many areas over the past two decades
serves the realistic interests of the two countries and benefits,
peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region and in the world at
large, he added.
</P>
<P>
Liang also expressed the hope that young people of both countries
will work for the growth of Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
Japanese ambassador to China Sakutaro Tanino told the audience
that Japan's new cabinet will maintain and develop friendly and
cooperative relations with China.
</P>
<P>
The gathering was organized by the China Association for
International Friendly Contact and Beijing Foreign Studies
University.  
