<HEADLINE> Two More Cubs For Chinese Tigers (Updated) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A white tiger gave birth to
two cubs several hours after having given birth to four early
Tuesday, according to a zookeeper in the Chinese city of Panyu in
Guangdong Province, south China.
</P>
<P>
The zookeeper at the Xiangjiang Wild Animal Park had said that
they did not expect any more for the mother, whose name is
"Kaili", after the four were born.
</P>
<P>
But then two new ones appeared three hours later, something
that has never happened before, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li Yangwen of the Chinese Association for the Protection of
Wild Animals said that Kaili seems to have set a world record.
</P>
<P>
This brings her total number of cubs to ten. She had four
last April.
</P>
<P>
Zoologists say that it is very rare for a white tiger to give
birth twice in one year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
