<DOCNO> XIE19981007.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With British Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said that the smooth transfer of power of Hong Kong last
year marked a new chapter in Sino-British relations and Blair's
visit to China is the first by the British Prime Minister of a
Labor Party government since the establishment of diplomatic
relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he believes that Blair's visit will help push
cooperation between the two countries forward in various areas.
</P>
<P>
Blair said that there has been enormous change in China since
he last visited the country 10 years ago, and that the successful
transfer of power of Hongkong marked a new era in relations
between Britain and China. His friendly exchanges on a broad range
of issues with Chinese leaders have laid a good foundation for
furthering bilateral relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that both China and Britain, as permanent members of
the U.N. Security Council, shoulder an important responsibility
for maintaining world peace and for the common progress of mankind.
</P>
<P>
Blair said that the Queen and the British people are looking
forward to Jiang's state visit to Britain next year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his thanks to Queen Elizabeth for the
invitation and asked Blair to convey his regards to the Queen.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also discussed China's economic situation and the fight
against floods this year and thanked the British government for
its aid to flood-ravaged areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
