<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-British Aviation Memo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China and Britain signed a memo
of understanding on civil aviation today, with British Prime
Minister Tony Blair attending the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The agreement allows airlines in both countries to open two
Shanghai-London flights a week. They can also increase flights on
other routes between China and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Civil Aviation Administration of China say
they believe the memo will increase exchanges between the aviation
sector of the two countries and promote bilateral economic and
trade cooperation, tourism and personnel exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
