<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Still Considers Attending APEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie is still considering to attend the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation forum (APEC) summit to be held in Malaysia next month,
Minister/State Secretary Akbar Tanjung said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters before attending a limited cabinet
meeting, the minister said that the president has to consider his
presence at the APEC summit because he is busy with state duties
at home.
</P>
<P>
"Because he is busy at home, he has to consider attending the
summit," Akbar said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported previously that the president would not attend
the summit because he is busy with state duties at home.
</P>
<P>
"So the president has not decided yet?" asked reporters.
</P>
<P>
"He is still considering," Akbar answered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
