<HEADLINE> German Inflation Remains at Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany's annual inflation rate
remained at 0.8 percent in September, the lowest level since the
German reunification in 1990, the Federal Statistics Office announced
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Comparing with August, consumer prices in Germany dipped 0.2
percent due to seasonal factors such as declines in prices for
fruit and tourist travel.
</P>
<P>
The annual inflation rates in Germany moved steadily downwards
since April when consumer prices increased by 1.4 percent from the
same month of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
