<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, Kuwait Agree to Diversify Trade Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and Kuwait have agreed
to improve and diversify their bilateral trade links as both
countries have various unexplored areas to expand trade and
investment relationship, said an official handout here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A visiting Kuwait-Bangladesh parliament friendship group, which
called on Bangladeshi Commerce and Industries Minister Tofael
Ahmed Tuesday, said that they came to the country with a mission
to strengthen the friendship between the two countries through
cementing the trade relationship.
</P>
<P>
The group leader requested the minister for bilateral
agreements on avoidance of double taxation and promotion and
protection of investment.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is a promising market and has a wide range of
opportunities to set up joint venture projects in the untapped
areas, the handout quoted group members as saying.
</P>
<P>
The general people, investors, exporters and importers of
Kuwait are unaware of the potentialities of Bangladesh and stress
the need of frequent visits by trade bodies and related government
organizations, they added.
</P>
<P>
"We have trade and economic agreement with Kuwait which could
be geared up through setting up joint economic commission," the
Bangladeshi minister said, adding that Bangladesh is also
interested in signing agreements with Kuwait on avoidance of
double taxation and promotion and protection of investment.
</P>
<P>
"We are offering an attractive incentive package for foreign
investment and Kuwaiti investors are highly welcome to invest in
Bangladesh," the minister stated.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral trade between the two countries is only 6 million
U.S. dollars which could be increased by manifold "if we could
explore the areas purposefully", he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
