<HEADLINE> Congo's Kabila Visits Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- President of the Democratic
Republic of Congo Lauren Kabila is now on a two-day official
visit to Nigeria, probably to seek assistance for his fighting
against the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Kabila, who arrived at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International
Airport in Nigerian capital Abuja Tuesday, was met by the Head of
State, General Abdulsalam Abubakar, the chief of General Staff,
Rear Admiral Mike Akhigbe and other top officials.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders later held talks in the State House, the
details of which were not known.
</P>
<P>
Reports said they discussed civil crisis in Congo and possible
assistance from Nigeria, but presidential sources were not
immediately available for comment.
</P>
<P>
Kabila, who came to power last year through a rebel action has
been facing fierce military attacks from the Tutsi rebels and
their allies in the last two months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a report from Congo said the rebels are
concentrating forces for a major battle to seize government's
stronghold in the east Kindu, which they claimed would decide the
future of the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
