<HEADLINE> Share Prices Soaring on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices climbed by a big
margin on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday on expectations of more
cut in global interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) soared by 30.09 points
to 921.57 points in active transactions, recovering through the
900 points level after fluctuating below it for nearly a week.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover surged to 160.03 million units valued at 216.78
million Singapore dollars (129.81 million U.S. dollars). Rises
outstripped falls 208 to 36 while 240 counters were unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block in transactions was a 16.19 million units
parcel of Yan DH. SembCorp remained the second most heavily traded
stock with a volume of 11.22 million units. L&AMP;M was next with 8.58
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F led ascent of the day with a rise of 95 cents to 7.35
Singapore dollars at close. SIA F moved up 85 cents to 8.95
Singapore dollars. Transmarco was up 84 cents to end at 2.20
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 again was the biggest loser of the
day as it fell 30 cents to 14.30 Singapore dollars. Labroy w02 was
the second biggest loser with a slide of four cents to 0.60
Singapore dollars. Times Pub shed four cents as well to end at
1.91 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also attributed Wednesday's rally to stronger regional
markets, saying market sentiment picked up as the rally in Japan
and Hong Kong markets helped to propel local share prices upward.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
