<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Wednesday as the early
morning's uptrend on local buying was reversed by profit taking
later in the day.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index ended 3.55
points lower at 370.90, the all-share Emas Index shed 0.76 of a
point to 98.28, the Industrial Index lost 8.07 points to 733.25
and the Second Board Index shed 0.24 of a point to 91.52.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by 337 to 245 while 127
counters were unchanged, 207 untraded and 33 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 168.758 million shares valued at
244.842 million ringgit (about 64.432 million U.S. dollars) from
146.262 million shares worth 192.403 million ringgit (about 50.632
million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover increased to 162.413 million shares
valued at 234.989 million ringgit (about 61.839 million U.S.
dollars) from 139.426 million shares worth 179.681 million ringgit
(about 47.284 million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover declined to 6.345 million shares
worth 9.852 million ringgit (about 2.592 million U.S. dollars)
from Tuesday's 6.836 million shares valued at 12.722 million
ringgit (about 3.347 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover decreased to 2.012 million shares worth
3.460 million ringgit (about 0.91 million U.S. dollars) from 9.302
million shares totaling 4.739 million ringgit (about 1.247 million
U.S. dollars) on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
