<HEADLINE> Air Portugal to End Business in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Macao office of Air Portugal
will be closed on October 31, according to a weekly
Portuguese-language newspaper based in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The last flight of Air Portugal will leave Macao on October 31,
the newspaper said, adding that the air company will maintain
necessary services for customers who have booked seats.
</P>
<P>
Observers say the close of the office is connected with the air
company's losses in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Air Portugal started business in Macao in April of 1996.
