<HEADLINE> 27 Fall Ill Due to Adulterated Oil in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- About 27 people in Udayapur
and Khotang districts of eastern Nepal fell ill seriously late
last month after eating food items cooked with adulterated oil,
the official RSS news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
They fell ill after taking food at a feast, which was cooked
with the Rocket-brand oil manufactured in Nepal, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The patients, 13 in Khotang district and about 14 in
neighboring Udayapur district, were said to be in critical
condition as doctors were still not available there.
</P>
<P>
RSS said that police had detained the owner of the shop selling
the adulterated oil.
</P>
<P>
The adulterated oil, which had caused much panic in Nepal in
the past few weeks, is yet to be removed from the market.
</P>
<P>
One person in Kanchanpur district of far-western Nepal died
recently of dropsy developed after taking adulterated mustard oil
in India, where the adulterated mustard oil had claimed more than
50 lives and caused over 2,000 cases of dropsy by early this
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
