<HEADLINE> New Set of Stamps to Be Issued in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A new set of stamps will be issued
by the Macao Posts and Telecommunications Department (CTT) on
October 9, CTT director Carlos Lopes said at a news conference
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Featuring the Temple Kun Iam in Macao, each of the four stamps
has a face value of 3.5 patacas (about 0.44 U.S. dollars). Some
1.9 million pieces will be issued for each kind.
</P>
<P>
Temple Kun Iam is more than 370 years old and one of the most
famous and impressive temples in Macao. It has fascinating halls,
pavilions, gardens, color paintings, wood and rock engravings.
</P>
<P>
The temple has been a very popular place with Buddhist monks,
poets, artists and tourists.
</P>
<P>
CTT plans to issue 13 sets of stamps this year, with nine sets
having been issued up to now. 
</P>
