<HEADLINE> DPRK to Return Remains of U.S. Soldiers Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic
of Korea (DPRK) Thursday will return the remains of several
U.S. soldiers killed in the 1950-53 Korean War, the United States
Forces in South Korea said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The returning ceremony will be held at the truce village of
Panmunjom inside the Demilitarized Zone that separates the Korean
peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The remains were found by a joint U.S.-DPRK team operating in the
country since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the remains of 15 U.S.soldiers have been returned by
the DPRK since the joint recovery operation began.
</P>
<P>
More than 50,000 American soldiers were killed in the 1950-53
Korean War and some 8,100 of them remains unaccounted for. 
</P>
</TEXT>
