<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bahrain, Iran To Restore Full Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Bahraini Minister of Labour
and Social Affairs Abdulla Al Shola has said Bahrain and Iran have
agreed to restore their relations to ambassadorial level.
</P>
<P>
Shola, who was on a visit to Iran, made the announcement in an
exclusive interview carried by the Wednesday edition of the Al
Itihad daily of the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
He said an agreement was reached after intensive talks in
Tehran Tuesday with Iranian officials to reciprocate ambassadors
soon. But he did not say when.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain and Iran recalled their ambassadors in May 1996 after a
row over Bahrain's unrest - a 19-month wave of riots Manama said
had Iranian backing.
</P>
<P>
Iran has denied the charge.
</P>
<P>
Shola said that Bahrain has a keen interest in maintaining
"positive" relations with Tehran and in improving regional
security in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that he has also signed a memorandum of
understanding for mutual political and economic cooperation with
his Iranian counterpart Hossein Kamali. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
