<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Company Donates to Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China Resources (Holdings) Co.
Ltd., a major Chinese-funded company in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), donated five million yuan today to
help rebuild homes for flood victims.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Civil Affairs will distribute the funds to a
number of provinces, including Hunan and Hubei provinces in
central China, Jiangxi in the east, and Heilongjiang and Jilin in
the northeast, as well as the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region in
the north.
</P>
<P>
The company also donated three million yuan to flood-ravaged
inland areas in August.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the company's 50th anniversary. All funds
originally planned for celebrations will go to flood relief
efforts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
