<HEADLINE> China's Guangdong Business Fair Opens in LA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangdong Province
Tuesday introduced more than 150 investment projects to the
U.S. business community at a trade show in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
The four-day 98' Guangdong Business Fair for Economic
Development, Technology and Trade, the second since 1994, has
drawn some 500 American officials and potential investors.
</P>
<P>
More than 120 booths are showcasing products from Guangdong and
one special booth is from U.S. Department of Commerce, which
provides information on exporting from the United States to China.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong is located in the southernmost of China's mainland,
adjacent to Hong Kong and Macao. Its foreign trade in 1997 was 130
billion U.S. dollars, accounting for 40 percent of China's total.
</P>
</TEXT>
