<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scenic Area to Be Built Near Largest Saltwater Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A national-level tourist area
will be built near China's largest saltwater lake in the
northwestern province of Qinghai, according to the China National
Tourism Administration (CNTA).
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Lake covers an area of 4,583 square kilometers and is
about 200 kilometers from the capital city of Xi'ning. A number of
attractive mountains, islands, and old towns are scattered around
the lake.
</P>
<P>
But not very many tourists head for the lake because of
a short tourism season, incomplete tourist facilities and cold
weather over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The CNTA and the Qinghai provincial government have jointly
drawn up a plan to develop tourism resources, build hotels
catering to average folks as well as a convention center and
villas, and operate a luxury tourist ship on the lake.
</P>
<P>
The lake will become a large tourist resort, said a CNTA
official, adding that this is a key project among the country's
massive efforts to speed up the development of ecological tourism
resources in 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
