<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Picked to Lead ACP Council of Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenya has been endorsed to
preside over the Council of Ministers of the African, Caribbean
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Kenya will assure the east African country
of full participation and negotiation in the ACP-European Union
cooperation, East African Standard quoted Kenyan Minister for
Planning and National Development George Saitoti as saying.
</P>
<P>
On his arrival from the 68th session of the ACP-EU Council of
Ministers meeting in Brussels, Belgium on Tuesday, Saitoti said
that during the future negotiations, the ACP group will call upon
the EU to initiate immediate debt relief measures including
outright debt write-off.
</P>
<P>
The ACP-EU cooperation was initiated in 1975 with the
intention of developing an arrangement that focuses on trade and
financial assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
