<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Install 1,000 New Phone Lines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has signed a
cooperation pact with a Canadian telecommunications company to
install 1,075 telephone lines in its northwestern region of
Kagera.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned Tanzania Telecommunications Company Limited
(TTCL) signed the pact in Dar es Salaam Tuesday with Sasktel
International of Canada for the implementation of a telephone
project in the Lake Victoria region.
</P>
<P>
Under the four-billion-Shilling (about six million U.S.
Dollars) project, to be executed in two years, new telephone
facilities will be installed in Ngara, Biharamulo. Karagwe and
Bukoba Rural Districts, local media said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The project, to be financed by the Canadian International
Development Agency (CIDA), is part of Tanzania's
Telecommunications Restructuring Program which started in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, TTCL Managing Director Adolar Mapunda said that the
company will start operating cellular phones services early next
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
