<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Transport Safety Assured After Train Speed Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Passenger safety will be
absolutely assured when train speeds were increased earlier this
month, according to Chang Guozhi, chief dispatcher of the Ministry
of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has made full preparations for the higher speeds,
with an emphasis on transportation safety, he said.
</P>
<P>
Rail-crossing conditions have been improved on the Beijing-Harbin,
Beijing-Guangzhou, and Beijing-Shanghai lines, with 456
flyovers now completed and 1,453 kilometers of fenced sections on
the Beijing-Harbin, Beijing-Guangzhou, Beijing-Shanghai, and
Beijing-Qinhuangdao lines.
</P>
<P>
Bridges and roadbeds also have been consolidated.
</P>
<P>
Chang said that new technological standards will be implemented
to accommodate the faster trains, and railway transport workers
have all received special training.
</P>
<P>
"Sound operational safety will be maintained on the railways," he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
