<DOCNO> XIE19981007.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Loses $600M Due to Gemstone Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Zambia is losing 600 million
U.S. Dollars annually through illegal exports of gemstones
especially emeralds.
</P>
<P>
A report issued recently by the U.N. Economic Commission for
Africa (ECA) said that tracking the performance of the gemstone
sub-sector in Zambia is a very difficult exercise due to informal
operations and the bad record of small miners in adhering to tax
obligations.
</P>
<P>
In contrast to the value of gemstones being smuggled out of
the country, Zambia earned only 10.3 million Dollars and 13.8
million Dollars respectively in 1996 and 1997, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's Copperbelt Development Association (CBA) has said
that while drawing up policies for the mining sector, the
government should include gemstones into these policies instead
of concentrating on copper alone.
</P>
<P>
CBA publicity secretary Tim Kondolo complained that precious
stone mining on the Copperbelt is still in its infancy in spite
of having been going on for more than 30 years.
</P>
<P>
If properly exploited, the gemstone industry has the potential
of becoming a major foreign exchange earner next to copper, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The CBA official called on the Zambian government to improve
security in the area as this is an important step of attracting
investment in the sector.
</P>
<P>
On the on-going privatization of the Zambia Consolidated
Copper Mines (ZCCM), the ECA report said that the successful
transfer of the mines into private hands is the key to enhancing
not only the mining sector but the entire economy of the country.
</P>
<P>
It noted that while small mines have already been disposed of,
only the sale of bigger Nkana and Nchanga mines will attest the
government's commitment to the full privatization of the mining
sector.
</P>
<P>
"The mines sold so far are considered as small cows in
Zambia's mining pen and the world is waiting for the sale of
Nkana and Nchanga copper mines, the fattest milk cows," said the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981007.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Confident of Reaching Tax Revenue Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Although the growth rate of its
industrial and commercial tax revenues so far this year has been
lower than in the past few years, China will still be able to
reach this year's target of increasing revenues by 80 billion yuan
(9.6 billion U.S. dollars), according to sources from the State
Tax Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China's industrial and commercial tax
revenues reached 515 billion yuan (62 billion U.S. dollars) in the
first eight months, up 7.9 percent over the same period last year
or an increase of 37.7 billion yuan (4.5 billion U.S. dollars),
60.7 percent of this year's targeted amount.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the State Administration of
Taxation, in the first half of the year revenue increase basically
matched the country's economic growth, with an 8.8 percent growth
in industrial and commercial tax revenues, higher than the
country's 7 percent GDP growth for the same period.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the Asian financial crisis and slumping
domestic demand are among the major causes of the slow revenue
growth.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few months the country's taxation system stepped
up supervision of tax levies and recovered overdue taxes worth
17.3 billion yuan (2 billion U.S. dollars), and at the same time
disposed of many tax evasion cases.
</P>
<P>
Vice-director of the SAT Lu Renfa said that with full support
from the State Council and the expected recovery of the economy
in the second half, the target of increasing revenues
by 80 billion yuan this year can be achieved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981007.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WFP Project to Benefit Poor Women In Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Over 36,000 poverty-stricken
woman in northwest China's Gansu Province are expected to gain
literacy and escape the grips of poverty over the next three
years, thanks to a new World Food Program (WFP) development
project launched a few days ago.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will be carried out in 13 townships in
Guyuan Prefecture, one of the poorest areas in the province, will
help teach 36,435 women how to read and write, and arm them with
practical skills needed to achieve a better life.
</P>
<P>
The women will be eligible for loan of 1,000 yuan (125 US
dollars) each to start small businesses in areas such as
cultivating cash crops and breeding domesticated animals.
</P>
<P>
More than 200,000 farmers in the prefecture have benefited from
a previous WFP poverty relief project implemented in 1994,
according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981007.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese Eurobond Issue Makes a Hit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Amid the world financial market,
turmoil, Lebanon on Tuesday recorded a sell-out when it went ahead
with the issue of a new 100 million U.S. dollar Eurobond, the
Daily Star newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The issue, which carries an interest yield of 8.75 percent
over a seven-year period, was launched by the U.S.-based
international financial group Merrill Lynch, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
This is Lebanon's third Eurobond issue in one year, after two
successful borrowings of 1 billion dollars in March and 350
million dollars in September.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese government planned to borrow a total of 2 billion
dollars on international financial market within this year in an
effort to restructure its national debt, which is predominated by
the high interest rate Lebanese pound.
</P>
<P>
Fuad Sinyoura, Lebanese minister of state for financial
affairs, said that 42 percent of the buyers of this issue were
non-Lebanese, as four Lebanese banks bought substantial quantities
of the Eurobond.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said that the strong demand for the new issue
came shortly after the news was leaked that Lebanon's Army
Commander Emile Lahoud has been given the nod of approval from
Syria to become the country's next president.
</P>
<P>
During the Lebanese-Syrian summit meeting on Monday, Syrian
President Hafez al-Assad and his Lebanese counterpart Elias Hrawi
agreed that Lebanon's constitution be amended to clear way for the
succession of Lahoud to Hrawi's post.
</P>
<P>
Syria, with 35,000 troops deployed in Lebanon, is believed to
be the main power broker and only king-maker in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
