<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Elected MPs Remain at 223 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- There remain only 223 parliament
representatives out of the 485 elected in the 1990 general
election in Myanmar, according to a military official.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Thein Swe, head of the Department of Bureau of
Strategic Studies of the Ministry of Defense, disclosed at a press
conference here Wednesday that of the 485 elected MPs, 27 were
dead, 61 resigned and 174 removed, indicating that the remainder
does not constitute half of the total number elected.
</P>
<P>
Of the remainder, 147 are from the National League for
Democracy (NLD) party, he said.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on some events which have taken place since April
this year, the official said that "the NLD has been deliberately
employing all kinds of tactics and pursuing a course that would
result in confrontation and collision with the government."
</P>
<P>
Regarding NLD's recent unilateral formation of the People's
Parliament, he also warned that the government will be tolerating
the unlawful acts with magnanimity as long as there is no harm to
the state and the people.
</P>
</TEXT>
