<HEADLINE> Ticket Sales for Asian Games Slower Than Expected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Ticket sales for the 13th Asian
Games have been slowed by uncertainties over the construction of
a sports complex, officials said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Asian Games Preparation Committee said ticket
sales are slower than expected, primarily because of the delays
in finishing off the venues for the games, particularly the Muang
Thong Thani Sports Complex in the suburbs of Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has yet to decide on buying 540 opening-closing
ceremonies tickets valued at 4.1 million baht (105,000
U.S.dollars); likewise, Japan has delayed their purchase of 2,230
tickets worth 11.2 million baht (287,000 dollars). Local sales
are also slow, dropping from 800,000-900,000 baht (20,512
dollars-23,076 dollars) to 100,000-150,000 baht (2,564
dollars-3,846 dollars) a day.
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the most popular sports -- badminton, basketball,
amateur boxing, soccer, gymnastics, Sepak Takraw, swimming, table
tennis, and volleyball -- will go on saleas of October 15, while
other tickets will be available from November 1.
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the opening ceremony are fully booked but there
are still tickets for the closing ceremony. 
</P>
