<HEADLINE> China To Tighten Control Over Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China is currently tightening
controls over the use of recently issued treasury bonds valued at
100 billion yuan in order to help ensure fulfillment of this
year's eight percent economic growth target.
</P>
<P>
According to today's People's Daily, 17 inspection teams will
be dispatched to 27 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
to oversee the effort, according to Zeng Peiyan, minister of the
State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
The most recent treasury bond issue was supported by an equal
amount of special bank loans. Related funds will be earmarked for
infrastructure construction projects designed to boost domestic
demand and offset the negative impact of financial crisis sweeping
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Investing such a large amount of money in such a short period
of time is unprecedented, said Zeng, adding that strict
supervision will be necessary to properly implementing the
investment plan.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance recently announced regulations
governing the supervision and timely placement of funds. 
</P>
