<HEADLINE> Chinese Woman Gives Birth to Test-Tube Baby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A 46-year old woman from
northeast China's Liaoning Province gave birth to a test-tube baby
girl weighing 3.9 kg recently.
</P>
<P>
The woman named Zhang became the oldest Chinese woman to bear a
test-tube baby.
</P>
<P>
Zhang was unable to conceive following oviduct surgery carried
out in 1983. Doctors introduced in vitro fertilization and
successfully implanted a fertilized egg into the woman's womb
early last week.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the Shenyang Reproduction Medical Technology
Research Center have successfully performed dozens of implantation
operations over the past three years. The first tube-baby born at
the center is 30 months old. 
