<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Tea Culture Exchange Center Set to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A new Tea Culture Exchange
Center will open in Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang
Province, in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The center, which covers 1.4 ha, is the second phase project at
the Chinese Tea Museum. The center, which will be completed at a
cost of 28 million yuan (3.4 million U.S. dollars), will promote
international tea culture exchanges and seminars.
</P>
<P>
The center is located on the southern slopes of Jiqing Hill
near West Lake, the home of famous Dragon Well Tea.
</P>
<P>
The center consists an academic conference hall equipped with
simultaneous interpretation equipment, a computerized reference
center offering photographs and written materials and an
exhibition hall.
</P>
<P>
The center also has a tea garden to facilitate research and
experimentation conducted by tea experts and scholars. 
</P>
