<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Flood Statistics at a Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are preliminary
statistics for damage caused by severe floods in Bangladesh
compiled by the government, U.N. agencies, non-governmental
organizations and trade bodies:
</P>
<P>
Districts affected: 52 (out of 64)
</P>
<P>
Deaths: 1,050
</P>
<P>
Highways and roads damaged: 15,000 kilometers
</P>
<P>
Embankment damaged: 2,000 kilometers
</P>
<P>
Crops damaged: 1,565,390 hectares
</P>
<P>
Houses damaged: 550,000
</P>
<P>
Educational institutions damaged: 24,000
</P>
<P>
Industrial units damaged: 1,200
</P>
<P>
Bridges and culverts damaged: 20,500
</P>
<P>
Tubewells damaged: 300,000
</P>
<P>
Preliminary estimated loss: 3.4 billion U.S. dollars
</P>
<P>
Foreign aid so far committed: 10.15 billion taka (211.43
million
dollars)
</P>
<P>
These statistics were compiled in accordance with up-to-date
media reports.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh experienced the worst-ever flood in a century during
the July-September period this year. All together, the deluge
lasted for two and a half months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
