<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, October 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- China's central bank chief urged world financial
leaders at a meeting here to strengthen the architecture of the
international monetary system so as to effectively prevent and
resolve financial crises. (US-China-Monetary System)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Michel Camdessus, Managing Director of the
International Monetary Fund (IMF), Tuesday said the whole
financial system, not just individual country, was now sunk in
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session of the IMF-World Bank Annual
Meeting, Camdessus said, "We are speaking not just of countries in
crisis, but of a system in crisis, a system not yet sufficiently
adapted to the opportunities and risks of globalization."
(IMF-Financial Crisis)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazil's exports this year might rise by 3-4
percent, much lower than the 11-12 percent expected by the
government earlier this year, the Brazilian Foreign Trade Chamber
said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that Brazil's trade deficit had reached 801
million U.S. dollars in September. (Brazil-Trade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina's exports to Arab countries have
reached nearly one billion U.S. dollars for the past nine years,
the Argentine Foreign Ministry said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It said that the trade between the two sides has grown from 365
million dollars to 1.28 billion dollars, of which 90 percent was
Argentine exports. (Argentina-Arab World-Trade)  
</P>
</TEXT>
