<HEADLINE> Mongolia Holds State Funeral for Slain Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia held a state funeral
Wednesday for Sanjaasurengiin Zorig, minister of infrastructure
development in the ad interim government.
</P>
<P>
Zorig, 36, was stabbed to death Friday night at his home by two
burglars, a man and a woman.
</P>
<P>
The burglars made away with some money and some jewelry.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian President Nachagyn Bagabandy, Chairman of the State
Great Hural Radnaasumberel Gonchigdorj and ad interim Prime
Minister Tsakhiagiin Elbegdorj attended the funeral.
</P>
<P>
The murder of Zorig, a potential candidate for prime minister,
might be politically motivated, an official at the presidential
office said at a press conference on Monday.
</P>
<P>
At an emergency meeting last Saturday, President Bagabandy
asked Prime Minister Elbegdorj to track down the murderers, who
are still at large. 
</P>
</TEXT>
