<HEADLINE> 140 Afflicted With Hepatitis B in Nepali District </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- One hundred and forty people
in Parsa district, central Nepal, have been afflicted with
hepatitis B since 1992, The Kathmandu Post reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
All blood donors in the district have been compulsorily tested
for hepatitis B since 1992 and 25 out of 10,000 people are found
positive for the infectious disease, the English-language daily
said.
</P>
<P>
About a dozen people have died of the disease since 1992, it
added.
</P>
<P>
Hepatitis is among the diseases which seriously affect human
lives in the Himalayan kingdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
