<HEADLINE> U.S. to File Anti-Subsidy Case Against India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The United States has decided
to file an anti-subsidy case and initiate anti-dumping proceedings
against elastic rubber tape exports from India, a government
official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first such case by the United States against
India. The results of the investigations into the subsidies are
expected to be out around November 12 this year and a preliminary
report of the anti-dumping proceedings around January 25 next
year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Both moves have serious implications for India's exports and
are likely to put subsidy schemes in trouble, he said.
</P>
<P>
The European Union has started several such cases against
Indian exports before.
</P>
<P>
Faced with a growing number of such cases and the resultant
threat to various export incentive schemes, India's Commerce
Ministry constituted a special cell last month to fight against
anti-subsidy and anti-dumping investigations concerning Indian
exports.
</P>
<P>
The Indian products against which anti-subsidy and anti-dumping
cases have been filed by the European Union include stainless
steel bright bars, steel wire ropes and cables, stainless steel
fasteners, antibiotics and polyester filament yarn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
