<HEADLINE> South Korean President Arrives in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Dae
Jung arrived in Japan Wednesday for a four-day state visit for
talks with Japanese leaders on the establishment of a new
bilateral partnership in the next century.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, his first trip to Japan since taking office
in February, Kim is expected to have an audience with Japanese
Emperor Akihito and Empress Michiko and hold summit talks with
Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
At the Seoul-Tokyo summit talks Thursday, Kim and Obuchi will
discuss a wide range of issues including Japan's apology for its
past colonial rule of the Korean Peninsula and bilateral
cooperation in economic and other areas, Japanese government
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are expected to issue a "joint declaration of a
new South Korea-Japan partnership for the 21st century" at the end
of their meeting, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi and Kim may also sign a provisional agreement on a new
bilateral fisheries pact Thursday, which the two countries,
through last-ditch efforts, managed to achieve in time for Kim's
visit.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday afternoon, Kim is scheduled to deliver a speech at
Japan's Diet (parliament).
</P>
<P>
The South Korean leader will also travel to Osaka in western
Japan before wrapping up his visit Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In Seoul, senior South Korean officials said Kim's trip will be
highlighted by non-economic issues despite economic issues are no
less important.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean people are observing the state visit with keen
interest, keeping a specially close eye on whether Japan will
apologize for its atrocities in the 1910-1945 colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, Japanese emperors and prime ministers have failed
to make official apology for Japan's atrocities and war crimes
against Koreans and the people in other nations countries in
history.
</P>
<P>
South Korean officials said they are expecting Japan to make a
"full apology" for the atrocities it committed against Korea and
the Korean people in history.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the officials hoped that Kim's visit will expand
offical dialogue channels between cabinet members of the two
countries in various fields such as defense, economy and culture.
</P>
</TEXT>
