<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes Drug Tablets in Shan State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
498,000 tablets of amphetamine stimulant drug in a raid in the
country's eastern Shan state late last month, official newspaper
The New Light of Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was made by a combined team of regional
intelligence unit, armymen and special anti-drug squad who raided
a house in Mekhong ward of Tachilek on September 26.
</P>
<P>
The local police station has taken action against two people in
connection with the case under Myanmar's Narcotic Drug and
Psychotropic Substances Law, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last month, the authorities also seized more than 1
million stimulant drug tablets in Kengtung of the same state and
took action against five people involved in the trafficking.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, nearly 9 million stimulant
drug tablets were confiscated by the Myanmar authorities in the
first nine months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
