<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WBA Can't Give Welterweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 6 (Xinhua) -- WBA won't be allowed to
award its vacant welterweight title to the winner of the bout
between its No.1 and No. 3 boxers, a state judge ruled today in
New Jersey, the United States.
</P>
<P>
The ruling came after the WBA's No. 2 contender, Jose Luis
Lopez, challenged the sanctioning, saying WBA was obligated to
let him fight for the title.
</P>
<P>
State Superior Court Judge Amos C. Saunders agreed, and
ordered that the WBA must let promoters bid on a fight between
Lopez and the No. 1 contender, Andrey Pestrayev of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The fight between Pestrayev and No. 3 James Page on October 10
can continue.
</P>
<P>
Main Events lawyer Patrick C. English said it was highly
unusual for the No. 2 contender to be excluded from a title fight
when the title is vacant.
</P>
<P>
The ruling from Saunders came Monday following a hearing in
his Passaic courtroom.
</P>
<P>
The WBA welterweight crown was vacated by Ike Quartey of Ghana
for a shot at the WBC welterweight belt November 21 against Oscar
De La Hoya. Lopez fought Quartey to a 12-round draw in October.
</P>
</TEXT>
