<HEADLINE> China State Development Bank Supports Northwest Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank (SDB),
China's largest policy bank, has contributed greatly to economic
development in the northwestern region with loans totaling 57.1
billion yuan since its establishment in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China, which consists of Shaanxi, Gansu and Qinghai
provinces, and the Ningxia Hui and Xinjiang Uygur autonomous
regions, accounts for more than a quarter of the nation's total
territory.
</P>
<P>
The bank has funded 257 construction projects in northwest
China since 1994, which involve a total investment of 169.3
billion yuan, including some 69.4 billion yuan of loans from the
bank.
</P>
<P>
The funds have been used to support projects in power
generation, coal, petroleum, natural gas, railway, nonferrous
metals, civil aviation and chemical industries.
</P>
<P>
The bank granted loans totalling 10.2 billion yuan to the
region between January-August this year, up over 60 percent on the
same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
SDB Vice-President Yao Zhongmin has pledged that the bank will
continue to support the development in the region in order to
narrow the gap between eastern and western China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
