<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Province Strengthens Wildlife Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A set of wildlife protection
regulations issued by east China's Zhejiang Province provides a
solid legal basis for protection efforts and use of related
resources.
</P>
<P>
The regulations includes concrete stipulations governing
management, hunting, raising and the use of wildlife resources.
</P>
<P>
The province is home to 123 animal species under state
protection and 45 species under provincial protection.
</P>
<P>
The regulations were introduced to curb activities involving
excessive hunting and poaching of wild animals.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's efforts to protect wildlife has included the
establishment of 10 nature reserves covering 60,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Activities such as the annual "Love-the-Bird Week" have
also helped to improve the awareness of local residents concerning
the need to protect wildlife. 
