<HEADLINE> Tianjin Plans Second Phase of Power Project Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Tianjin, the
leading industrial base in north China, is preparing to begin
second phase construction at the Panshan Power Plant which will be
the largest plant in the region when completed.
</P>
<P>
The project, scheduled for completion in the year 2003 at an
estimated cost of 5.4 billion yuan, will feature two 600,000-kw
generating units. The plant will be the largest facility of its
kind in the country to use generators manufactured domestically.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin currently has a generating capacity of 2.5 million kw,
including some 1.5 million kw added since 1983.
</P>
<P>
Two 500,000-kw generating units were installed during the first
phase construction at Panshan. 
</P>
