objections.
</P>
<P>
Asahi:
</P>
<P>
-- The Japanese government is considering submitting to the
next regular Diet session a draft revision of the Alien
Registration Law that would abolish fingerprinting for all foreign
residents in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- Japan's largest automaker Toyota Motor Corp. will help 70
major parts makers in Southeast Asia in fund raising. 
</P>
