<HEADLINE> China Building Largest Metallurgical Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Shanghai
Krupp Stainless Steel Co., Ltd., the largest Sino-foreign joint
metallurgical venture, began recently in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The project is funded by the Shanghai Pudong Iron and Steel
(Group) Co., Ltd. and Krupp &AMP; Thyssen of Germany with more than
1.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
It will have a designed annual production capacity of 440,000
tons of stainless steel plate and will be China's largest
stainless steel production base by early the next century.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of work will use 300 million U.S. dollars for a
facility with an annual production capacity of 72,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
It is predicted that the venture will help China in alleviating
its shortage of stainless steel plate. Domestic producers only
provide 20 percent of the stainless plate needed in China and the
country has to import 400,000 tons of stainless plate each year.
</P>
</TEXT>
