<HEADLINE> Gold Deposits Discovered in Peru-Ecuador Border Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Large gold deposits have been found
in the Condor mountain range, which is part of the disputed border
area between Peru and Ecuador, said a report Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report, issued by the International Conservation, a
non-governmental organization, said that the Condor mountain range
is a huge "gold belt".
</P>
<P>
The mountain range is a 70-kilometer-long border stretch, which
saw a military conflict between Peruvian and Ecuadoran troops in
1995.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the International Conservation discovered that the
mountain range also has deposits of other minerals.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of Peru and Ecuador have negotiated for a long time to
seek a peace accord between their countries.
</P>
<P>
But economic interests, instead of political considerations,
are reportedly the obstacle to a peaceful settlement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
