<HEADLINE> Unemployed People in Chinese City Going to Community Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China's social development has
brought great changes to people's ideas about jobs like community
services including nursing, washing, and cleaning.
</P>
<P>
The traditional view was that this kind of work was undignified
and many unemployed workers were unwilling to do it. But things
have changed and "it is far better than just staying idly at
home," according to Wang Ping, a 40-year-old women who was laid
off in the city of Tianjin and has taken to looking after a woman
who is above 90.
</P>
<P>
"It was quite difficult at first," Wang says, because the old
woman often complained, and she felt exhausted after a day's
work. But, now she is getting used to it, and they get along quite
well.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is an old industrial and commercial center in northern
China and changes in the economic and industrial structure have
meant that more than 320,000 workers have lost their jobs over the
past few years.
</P>
<P>
There are now many organizations that provide community service
jobs for unemployed people. The Tianjin Family Service Company is
one of them, which finds suitable jobs for over 300 people every
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
