<HEADLINE> Dalian's Fashion Festival Available on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A click of the mouse, and you
will be able to once again attend the Tenth Dalian International
Fashion Festival, which closed weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
A website opened recently on the Internet provides more people
with easy access to this year's largest Chinese fashion festival.
</P>
<P>
The fashion festival in the northeast China port city of Dalian
which started ten years ago has become an important annual
international event attracting growing numbers of overseas
traders, who this year accounted for a record 63 percent of all
participants.
</P>
<P>
The website will make the festival a continuous international
event, said Wang Zhenjiao, a Dalian computer network center
official, adding that the site has already received a large amount
of E-mail from abroad.
</P>
<P>
On-line service provides people with the history of the fashion
show and the lastest information on fashion trends, competitions
and symposiums.
</P>
<P>
The website also has been linked with other similar websites
around the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
