<HEADLINE> Shanghai Putting One Million Trees into Urban Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai plans to transplant
one million trees in its urban area over the next three years to
turn the city into a beautiful international metropolis in a move
funded by the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
About 15,000 big trees will be planted along 40 major streets
and scenic spots this year.
</P>
<P>
The trees will include gingko, beech, pine, and camphor mainly
brought from surrounding provinces.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has a dense population of about 13 million in a
375-sq.km. area and tree-planting is seen as a good means of
greening the city on a limited amount of land.  
</P>
</TEXT>
