cabinet meeting that Talas' remarks were "strange and untrue,"
adding that "facts are known that Jordan offered all possible
help to the Saudi (Arabian) forces as they passed through Jordan
with a military plane (during the war)."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Judeh expressed the cabinet's rejection to any
accusation against Jordan, especially at a time that the kingdom is
trying to help the region avoid a new catastrophe that might arise
from the current crisis between Syria and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian government hopes that such accusation and remarks
will not be repeated, he added.
